<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/36409372-dylan-crossen"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/36409372-dylan-crossen">Dylan Crossen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Weatherford&apos;s main citation for Genghis (or Chinggis) Kahn&apos;s personal life is &quot;The Secret History of the Mongols.&quot; He also references plenty of histor<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Weatherford's main citation for Genghis (or Chinggis) Kahn's personal life is "The Secret History of the Mongols." He also references plenty of historians and commentators from a variety of countries and time periods to get an idea of how the world perceived the Mongols.<br /><br />It's a fun dramatized narrative to read and I'd recommend it as a jumping off point for an interest in the Genghis and the Mongols. However, it is by no means a comprehensive text. Hope this helps friend! :D<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
