    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2589288949" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2589288949" />
    <a title="Adam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29075798-adam"><img alt="Adam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519711514p2/29075798.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2589288949?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adam" href="/user/show/29075798-adam">Adam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/40868770-genghis-khan-and-the-making-of-the-modern-world">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=audible">audible</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=story-4-star">story-4-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=narration-5-star">narration-5-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=read-2019">read-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2589288949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8763328677861363935">Review of the audiobook narrated by Jonathan Davis.<br/><br/>There is much about the history of the Mongols that I had learned only obliquely in the past so it was great to read a dedicated chronicle about them. It was an interesting mix of both a forward thinking culture and one which frightened the rest of the world with their barbarism (both real and imagined). Genghis Khan himself has a truly compelling story and the inability for the Mongols to sustain such a massive and influential empire is both a </span>
  <span id="freeText8763328677861363935" style="display:none">Review of the audiobook narrated by Jonathan Davis.<br /><br />There is much about the history of the Mongols that I had learned only obliquely in the past so it was great to read a dedicated chronicle about them. It was an interesting mix of both a forward thinking culture and one which frightened the rest of the world with their barbarism (both real and imagined). Genghis Khan himself has a truly compelling story and the inability for the Mongols to sustain such a massive and influential empire is both a mark of Genghis' greatness and how massive and ultimately unmanageable the Mongol nation grew to be.<br /><br />Jonathan Davis is a top notch narrator. This was a real treat for a nonfiction book where the standards for narration are lower. This is the second time I've listened to a book narrated by him and, despite not actually liking the story for the first, both times I've been impressed. He's now in the category of narrators where I would choose a book in part just because he was the narrator.<br /><br />Final verdict: 4 star story, 5 star narration, 4 stars overall</span>
  <a data-text-id="8763328677861363935" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


